article.headline: Indiana State 70, Valparaiso 68 (OT)
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- Tyson Schnitker hit a 3-pointer with five seconds left in overtime Thursday night, giving Indiana State a 70-68 victory over Valparaiso. The victory was the third in a row for the Sycamores (4-2), while the loss dropped Valparaiso to 0-5. The Sycamores were led by David Moss, who scored a season-high 27 points and hauled in a career-best 14 rebounds. Jerod Adler added 17 points and Schnitker finished with 10 points. Dan Oppland led the Crusaders with 25 points and 13 rebounds and was the only Valparaiso player in double figures. Valparaiso led 29-17 at halftime, but Indiana State rallied in the second half and tied the game at 55 on two free throws by Eric Gray with less than two minutes left in regulation. Moss hit two foul shots to put the Sycamores up 59-57 with 11 seconds to go in regulation before Oppland scored at the buzzer to send the game to overtime. In the extra period, a basket by Shawn Huff put Valparaiso up 68-67 before Schnitker's game-winning 3-pointer.
